WEBVTT

00:04.885 --> 00:07.064
Previously on The Affair...

00:07.065 --> 00:08.899
Do you remember
the first time you saw her?

00:08.900 --> 00:10.132
Like it was yesterday.

00:11.833 --> 00:13.087
I have to leave.

00:13.088 --> 00:15.458
We've lived together for half our lives.

00:15.459 --> 00:17.016
I'm in love with someone else.

00:17.017 --> 00:18.976
I want you to get the
fuck out of my house.

00:18.977 --> 00:20.420
What if I moved to Montauk?

00:20.421 --> 00:22.750
- Why?
- To be with you.

00:22.751 --> 00:25.205
Look, I know I was a jerk, but I...

00:25.206 --> 00:27.109
I just got out of three years in prison.

00:27.110 --> 00:29.324
I don't want what I used to.

00:29.325 --> 00:30.580
I just want a simple life.

00:30.581 --> 00:32.240
I just want to get back into teaching.

00:32.241 --> 00:33.583
I want to live with someone I love.

00:33.584 --> 00:35.243
You were the best thing
that ever happened to me.

00:35.244 --> 00:38.041
No, I, uh... I
want a divorce, Noah.

00:38.042 --> 00:39.239
How's Vik?

00:40.187 --> 00:41.645
He's good.

00:42.417 --> 00:44.999
He just got a major job offer in L.A.

00:45.000 --> 00:46.671
The children's hospital there.

00:46.672 --> 00:48.583
This fella's quite a catch.

00:48.584 --> 00:51.008
Handsome, polite, a doctor.

00:51.009 --> 00:54.666
Anyone would be an improvement
after your first husband.

00:54.667 --> 00:56.332
Noah's not doing well, huh?

00:56.333 --> 00:57.999
Well, he's downstairs.

00:58.000 --> 00:59.892
I'll tell him to leave right now.

00:59.893 --> 01:01.561
You do what you want, Helen.

01:01.562 --> 01:03.145
Because I get how this goes.

01:03.146 --> 01:04.172
He leaves now.

01:04.173 --> 01:05.541
Whenever he shows up with his bullshit,

01:05.542 --> 01:07.207
you let him right back fucking in.

01:07.208 --> 01:09.026
Why can't you just let him go?

01:09.027 --> 01:10.317
Thing is, for my whole life,

01:10.318 --> 01:12.664
I've had this idea that
I'm a good person,

01:12.665 --> 01:14.583
and, uh, it's not true.

01:14.584 --> 01:15.875
No, it's not.

01:15.876 --> 01:17.207
Good-bye.

01:17.208 --> 01:19.249
I killed Scott Lockhart.

01:19.250 --> 01:21.041
It wasn't Noah.

01:21.042 --> 01:24.066
That is why I let Noah back in.

01:24.067 --> 01:25.871
Because I felt like I owed him

01:25.872 --> 01:27.774
and I was trying to fix what I did.

01:27.775 --> 01:30.281
It was not because I loved him.

01:30.282 --> 01:31.925
I'll find you after work.

01:33.356 --> 01:35.049
Being a parent is hard.

01:35.050 --> 01:36.534
And I know we haven't done it perfectly,

01:36.535 --> 01:39.015
but I learned from my parents' mistakes,

01:39.016 --> 01:41.583
and your mother learned from hers,

01:41.584 --> 01:43.728
just as you'll learn from our mistakes.

01:43.729 --> 01:46.666
Until someone someday

01:46.667 --> 01:49.551
finally has a perfect childhood.

01:51.804 --> 01:53.391
Where we going, buddy?

